-- Emirates Islamic, Noor Islamic, Dubai Bank May Merge; Buy Amlak, 24/7 Says
-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 2010-10-13T04:46:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/emirates-islamic-noor-islamic-dubai-bank-may-merge-buy-amlak-24-7-says.html
A proposal to merge Emirates Islamic
Bank, the United Arab Emirates Islamic lender controlled by
Emirates NBD PJSC, with Dubai Bank and Noor Islamic Bank is
being considered, Emirates 24/7, citing an unidentified
government official.  The combined entity will bail out mortgage lender Amlak
Finance PJSC, according to the report. Emaar Properties PJSC,
the biggest shareholder in Amlak, is unlikely to provide more
money to the mortgage company, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  